<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<darktable_style version="1.0"><info><name>wb_kelvin_delta</name><description>WB Kelvin / tint UX wrapper (#102). Same temperature module as the existing temperature entry, but exposes photographic units instead of raw RGB coefficients. Two axes: --param kelvin_delta=V (range [-3000, 3000]; positive = warmer) and --param tint_delta=V (range [-200, 200]; positive = magenta-shifted, negative = green). Linear approximation: red_coeff *= 1 + kelvin_delta * 0.0001, blue_coeff inverse, green_coeff *= 1 + tint_delta * 0.0001. Daily-use accurate; not chromatic-adaptation-perfect (real CAT02/Bradford would be camera-primaries-aware). Useful for Lightroom-parity UX where users dial Kelvin/tint, not coefficients. The temperature entry is preserved for users who want raw coefficient control.</description></info><style><plugin><num>0</num><module>4</module><operation>temperature</operation><op_params>0000803f0000803f0000803f0000807f02000000</op_params><enabled>1</enabled><blendop_params>gz11eJxjYIAACQYYOOHEgAZY0QWAgBGLGANDgz0Ej1Q+dcF/IADRAGpyHQU=</blendop_params><blendop_version>14</blendop_version><multi_priority>0</multi_priority><multi_name></multi_name><multi_name_hand_edited>0</multi_name_hand_edited></plugin></style></darktable_style>
